data.title: Mas o Menos
data.text: Nothing spectacular about this Filipino restaurant, except perhaps that it is open on Sunday.  Like many Filipino buffet restaurants (or any buffet restaurant as a matter of fact), don't come to  eat within the last hour that before it closes.  They won't bring out any more fresh batch.

data.title: Good Food, Good Selection, Nothing Spectacular.
data.text: We recently visited this place on our most recent visit to San Diego and was surprised that this restaurant has really stayed stagnant and old. Last time we ate at Point Point Restaurant was several years ago and it was better then.... much better. The food were okay with nothing to brag about. I suggest you go somewhere else as this is not one of those WOW moment in a Filipino eatery. The food was not as hot as it should be amd the place was a little dirty or messy when we came.

data.title: Filipino Dishes
data.text: OK, sort of what you expect. My feet stuck to the floor as I walked. Not much steam coming out of the steam table at the food line. There are better places nearby, but it's OK.
